        -:  307:/* --- General R x C exact test (used for anything that is not 2x2) ---------
        -:  308: *
        -:  309: * The 2x2 machinery above cannot describe larger tables, so the R x C case
        -:  310: * is handled by direct enumeration of every contingency table that shares
        -:  311: * the observed row and column margins.  Under the null the probability of a
        -:  312: * table T with fixed margins is the multivariate hypergeometric
        -:  313: *
        -:  314: *      P(T) = (prod_i R_i!)(prod_j C_j!) / ( N! prod_ij t_ij! )
        -:  315: *
        -:  316: * The (two-sided) p-value is the sum of P(T) over all such T whose
        -:  317: * probability is <= P(observed).  Only two-sided is defined for R x C, so
        -:  318: * 'alternative' is ignored for larger tables (matching R's fisher.test). */
